		<p>QLC+ dark mode/theme.</p>
		<p>Very simple installation.</p>
		<p>See <a href="https://github.com/Xilef12000/qlcplus-dark-theme">https://github.com/Xilef12000/qlcplus-dark-theme</a> for more info.</p>
		<p>See <a href="https://www.instructables.com/QLC-Dark-Theme/">https://www.instructables.com/QLC-Dark-Theme/</a> for more info.</p>
		<h3>Step 1: Download the Stylesheet</h3>
		<p>Go to
			<a href="https://github.com/Xilef12000/qlcplus-dark-theme">https://github.com/Xilef12000/qlcplus-dark-theme</a>
			click on the right under the "Releases" tab on the latest version.
		</p>
		<p>Download the "Source code (zip)" file on the bottom.</p>
		<h3>Step 2: Unzipping</h3>
		<p>Unzip the folder.</p>
		<h3>Step 3: Copy the File</h3>
		<p>Copy the "qlcplusStyle.qss" file to the correct path:</p>
		<p>LINUX 
			<code>$HOME/.qlcplus</code>
		</p>
		<p>Windows 
			<code>C:\Users\YOURUSERNAME\QLC+\qlcplusStyle.qss</code>
		</p>
		<p>MacOS 
			<code>~/Library/Application Support/QLC+/qlcplusStyle.qss</code>
		</p>
		<p>Make sure that QLC+ is closed while performing this action.</p>
		<h3>Step 4: Finish</h3>
		<p>Restart QLC+.</p>
		<p>And QLC+ should start in dark-mode.</p>
